# Section parent class and CSS scoping

When creating or editing HTML / Markup , especially Shopify Sections

- Add a top-level parent class on the section wrapper using `section__<section-handle>` (example: `section__quote-block`).
- Scope all section CSS selectors under that parent class.
- Use descendant selectors for section elements (example: `.section__quote-block .quote-author`).
- Avoid unscoped element class rules in any CSS created
- Keep this pattern consistent for new sections by default.
